The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Monday, May 28, 2007

 Book launch

 Arun Shouries book, The Parliamentary System, will be released at Crossword, 7pm. To be followed by an interactive session with MLA Sougata Roy, General (retd) Shankar Roy Choudhury and Arun Shourie.

 Interface

 Seminar on The Meta Language and Transcription of Empirical Ayurveda, at Asiatic Society, 10.30am. 

 Ex-minister Karan Singh will speak on Thoughts, Facts and Comments at Sri Aurobindo Bhavan, 7pm. 

 Workshop

 Workshop on Kathak, to be conducted by Sudeshna Moulik, at EZCC, 11am to 5pm. 

 On stage

 Bharatanatyam performance by Anita Mallick, at Sisir Mancha, 6.30pm.

 Art watch

 Summer Show, an exhibition of art works by various artists from across India, at CIMA Gallery, 3pm to 7pm. 

 An exhibition of paintings by various artists, including Kartick Pyne, Prokash Karmakar and Sanat Kars, at Masters Collection Art Gallery, 11am to 7pm.

 Connoisseurs Choice at Genesis Art Gallery, noon to 7pm. 

 Rooted in Realism, an exhibition of drawings and paintings by Bhaskar Mukherjee, at Gallery Kanishkas, 2pm to 8pm. 




